               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1328" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1328" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1328" type="surname" value="WYNNE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1328" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD WYNNE</persName>
                  </hi>. I deal in cheap publications, and lire in Chichester-place, King's cross—on Friday evening, the 28th of July, the prisoner brought these twenty-six copies of Lloyd's Atlas—he asked if I wanted to buy any—I asked what he wanted for them—he said, "What would you give?"—I offered him 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he would not take that—I gave him 8<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I took them to Mr. Lloyd's next rooming, and marked them, so that I know them again—the prisoner came again to me, and I gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1329" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1329" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1329" type="surname" value="LLOYD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1329" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD LLOYD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am printer and publisher of Lloyd's Penny Atlas—this is my property—on Friday, the 28th of July, none of these numbers had been published—they are worth 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—the prisoner applied for employment, and was in the place where he could take these.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HUDDLESTON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you any partners? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—the prisoner has borne a good character.</p>
